<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-16-0797 </DOCNO><TEXT>The book facilitates access to the scientific and technical fundamentalsthe development of motor vehicle engines is based on. The physical andtechnical engineering principles needed for the design and constructionof combustion engines are compiled in twelve chapters and rounded offby a comprehensive collection of specific data and facts. The book isthe first of its kind to present a complete and at the same time concisesurvey of motor vehicle design and construction aspects. It is a valuableguide, dictionary and reference book addressed to vehicle constructionstudents and technical engineers. (orig.) With 750 figs., 77 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>